    "narrative": "The engine of our lineup today is undoubtedly **Mickey Moniak**, who leads all starters with a 75.98 efficiency score. A favorable matchup against the hittable Sasaki (5.52 xERA) combined with an elite +14% park factor and dynamic platoon advantage makes him our primary target for production. Similarly, **Corbin Carroll** remains a mandatory start; despite a tough matchup against Gausman, his elite xwOBA metrics and the premium stolen base upside keep his score at a high 71.33. We are also leaning heavily on the top-of-the-order aggressiveness of **James Wood**, whose 66.69 score is buoyed by a +10% order bonus, ensuring he maximizes his plate appearances against Ray.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who missed the starting cut with a 51.32 score. While he presents a solid floor, the optimizer prioritized the speed-weighted efficiency of **Jose Caballero** and the positional versatility of our infielders; **Pasquantino**\u2019s -15% penalty due to a challenging left-on-left dynamic platoon served as the primary tiebreaker. We are also exercising caution with **Jose Caballero** and **Kyle Karros**, both of whom carry significant order-based penalties (-6%) that suppress their otherwise favorable park environments. **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Austin Riley** are currently positioned at the lower end of our starting threshold, necessitating a close watch on their respective matchups against Schultz and Painter. With no weather-related delays flagged, the focus remains on navigating the difficult outings for **Jose Caballero** against Ragans and the defensive hurdles facing **Seiya Suzuki** and **Austin Riley** against elite pitch-framing catchers.",
